comment.body:
I have changed the implementation to debounce at store, before filtering and after `emit`ting `searchText`. This improves the situation greatly. 

But for superhuman typing speeds, still, there remains a problem. And, it's to do with the `emit` function's `setTimeout`.
```js
setTimeout(() => {
        this._eventQueue.forEach(evt => {
          EventEmitter.prototype.emit.call(this, evt);
        });
        this._eventQueue = [];
        this._eventTimer = null;
}, 50);
```

Basically, when keystrokes happen in between that 50ms, they tend to be lost. (Because store state had not changed and the changed value has not propagated to the component through `props`). You can verify this if you try typing "asdf" really fast, and note the missing key(s). If you move the timeout to a lower value, it progressively becomes better.

I know this would hardly ever make an impact for the vast majority of users, but I'm just noting it here because it impacts what I set out to do. If a solution for this can be recommended, I'd be more than happy to work on it as well.
